# API Standards

All endpoints must use versioning:
/api/v1/<resource>

Success response envelope:
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {},
  "message": "Human-readable confirmation"
}

Error response envelope:
{
  "success": false,
  "error": {
    "code": "ERROR_CODE",
    "message": "Human-readable description",
    "details": {}
  }
}

Standard error codes:
VALIDATION_ERROR   → 422
NOT_FOUND          → 404
UNAUTHORIZED       → 401
FORBIDDEN          → 403
CONFLICT           → 409
INTERNAL_ERROR     → 500
RATE_LIMITED       → 429

Rules:
- Never return raw ORM/database objects
- All list endpoints must support pagination: ?page=1&limit=20
- Pagination responses must include: total, page, limit, has_next
- Use correct HTTP status codes — never 200 for errors
- All inputs validated via Pydantic schemas before reaching the service layer
- Rate limiting required on all public-facing endpoints
